":"ImageService3","profile":"http://iiif.io/api/image/3/level0.json"}]}}]}],"annotations":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-02805/canvas/1/page/p1","type":"AnnotationPage","items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-02805/canvas/1/bd6888fb-3bd9-422b-85af-554b1da10daa","type":"Annotation","motivation":"commenting","body":[{"created":"2026-06-29T15:41:52.688Z","creator":"g","purpose":"commenting","type":"TextualBody","format":"text/html","value":"<p>Alma’s mannerisms once in the plan américain project her discomfort with Cyril’s brazen presentation. With the camera pulled back to this distance, less intimate than the scene’s previous close-ups and medium shots, the atmosphere is noticeably more stilted with the change in personal dynamic. As Cyril drops her hand, Alma leans away to an almost exaggerated extent. She proceeds to tap her finger to her chest, followed by rubbing her neck, then scratching the side of her nose, all outwardly conveying her internal anxiety.&nbsp;</p>"}],"target":{"type":"SpecificResource","source":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-02805/canvas/1","selector":{"type":"FragmentSelector","conformsTo":"http://www.w3.org/TR/media-frags/","value":"xywh=pixel:1106.5501008742435,220.43039677202427,296.9737726967046,610.7330195023537"}}}]}]}]}